   Management (CIKM), San Francisco, CA, OCT 27-NOV 01, 2013}},
Organization = {{Assoc Comp Machinery; ACM Special Interest Grp Informat Retrieval; ACM
   SIGWEB}},
Abstract = {{We study the problem of disinformation. We assume that an ``agent{''}
   has some sensitive information that the ``adversary{''} is trying to
   obtain. For example, a camera company (the agent) may secretly be
   developing its new camera model, and a user (the adversary) may want to
   know in advance the detailed specs of the model. The agent's goal is to
   disseminate false information to ``dilute{''} what is known by the
   adversary. We model the adversary as an Entity Resolution (ER) process
   that pieces together available information. We formalize the problem of
   finding the disinformation with the highest benefit given a limited
   budget for creating the disinformation and propose efficient algorithms
   for solving the problem. We then evaluate our disinformation planning
   algorithms on real and synthetic data and compare the robustness of
   existing ER algorithms. In general, our disinformation techniques can be
   used as a framework for testing ER robustness.}},
