   has made numerous changes to its operations to try to combat
   disinformation, and is a good example of what platforms can do. The
   Chinese information regime is a marvel of networked information control,
   and provokes questions about what a democracy should and should not do.
   The tactics used by these organizations can be grouped into six high
   level strategies: refutation, exposure of inauthenticity, alternative
