   identifying possible changes in their work routines. Twenty-four
   structured interviews were conducted with political consultants,
   information verifiers, journalists and digital media social network
   managers. It was evidenced that the changes in working protocols are
   still small, although all social actors have been directly affected by
   the impact of disinformation. There is no consensus neither on the
