   fake news, propaganda, conspiracy theories, and radicalizing content.
   However, lack ineffective image and video processing techniques has
   hindered research on YouTube. In this paper, we advocate the use of
   metadata in identifying such malicious behaviors. Specifically, we
   analyze metadata of videos (e.g., comments, commenters) to study a
   channel on YouTube that was pushing content promoting conspiracy
