Abstract = {{Democracy is often used as shorthand for liberal democracy. Despite such
   casual conflation, the two concepts remain importantly distinct. I argue
   that democracy unfettered by the constraints of liberal institutions and
   commitments gives rise to the proliferation of disinformation and to
   xenophobic populism. I draw upon Plato and the democracy of ancient
