   extent of the misleading information on COVID-19. Further, in-depth
   interviews were conducted with factcheckers, media professionals,
   academicians, and a psychologist to understand the purpose of
   disinformation and its impact on society at large. The study's findings
   propose that fact-checking is a crucial method to identify
   fake/misleading information, which can be counter acted by accurate and
