   Consisting of 40 news-style articles, the data was used to find out how
   a conspiracy theory about the virus being a possible man-made bioweapon
   was presented to the audience. The results indicate that the rhizomatic
   structure of COVID-19 conspiracy theories makes it possible to vary the
   narratives based on the platform where it is published and the target
