Abstract = {{In this policy brief, after an account of the historical-political
   context of Russia's recent aggressive actions, I examine the objectives,
   strategy, and tactics of Russia's information warfare, particularly as
   concerns eastern Europe and Syria, although also against selected
   western European states and the USA. Of special interest is the notion
   that Russia's disinformation is potent because it does not necessarily
   establish falsehoods as true, but rather pollutes political discourse
   such that news information consumers are led to doubt the very concepts
   of truth and objective political facts. I conclude by (a) discussing the
   impact this strategy has had-and will continue to have-on Europe's
   domestic politics, as well as on the global liberal order, and then (b)
