Month = {{APR 29}},
Abstract = {{In its first 30 years the world wide web has revolutionized the
   information environment. However, its impact has been negative as well
   as positive, through corporate misuse of personal data and due to its
   potential for enabling the spread of disinformation.
   As a large-scale collaborative platform funded through charitable
   donations, with a mission to provide universal free access to knowledge
   as a public good, Wikipedia is one of the most popular websites in the
   world. This paper explores the role of Wikipedia in the information
   ecosystem where it occupies a unique role as a bridge between informal
   discussion and scholarly publication. We explore how it relates to the
   broader Wikimedia ecosystem, through structured data on Wikidata for
   instance, and openly licensed media on Wikimedia Commons. We consider
