   Papua and West Papua, is a significant factor is this low ranking. While
   other parts of Indonesia enjoy relatively free media coverage, West
   Papua remains the most closed region to media access, particularly to
   foreign media. There are patterns of threats that implicate the safety
   and security of local journalists in the territory. A clearing house, an
   intricate red-tape system, was re-introduced in May 2019 to screen
   foreign journalists going to the region of West Papua. Journalists
   require a permit to go there. Security forces monitor the journalists
   during their work in the region. In the past decade, two journalists
   have been killed, multiple journalists have been assaulted and arrested,
