   only an individual or societal cost, but it can lead to significant
   economic losses or to risks to national security. Blockchain and other
   distributed ledger technologies (DLTs) guarantee the provenance and
   traceability of data by providing a transparent, immutable, and
   verifiable record of transactions while creating a peer-to-peer secure
   platform for storing and exchanging information. This overview aims to
   explore the potential of DLTs to combat digital deception, describing
   the most relevant applications and identifying their main open
   challenges. Moreover, some recommendations are enumerated to guide
   future researchers on issues that will have to be tackled to strengthen
