   that what are witnessing right now is a proliferation technology-powered
   disinformation, a completely new phenomenon for which intellectual,
   regulatory and research tools barely exist. We discriminate between
   complex technological, socio-economic and psychological factors involved
   in this proliferation and the emergence of a completely new information
   ecosystem. We argue that, as a result of the phenomenal success of their
   digital platform technologies, the big technological companies act as
   global despots of our times, whose alleged dominance is enabled by their
