Abstract = {{This study explores youth accuracy judgments of disinformative and
   nondisinformative claims. Analyses are based on a nationally
   representative youth (16-20 years old) survey experiment conducted in
   the Czech Republic in 2017. When they were exposed to posts regarding
   refugee crisis, young people were asked to judge the accuracy of the
   statements accompanying the posts. Motivated reasoning of youth depended
   primarily on the alignment with the posts and the ideology of
