Abstract = {{Social Networking has dominated the whole world by providing a platform
   of information dissemination. Usually people share information without
   knowing its truthfulness. Nowadays Social Networks are used for gaining
   influence in many fields like in elections, advertisements etc. It is
   not surprising that social media has become a weapon for manipulating
   sentiments by spreading disinformation. Propaganda is one of the
   systematic and deliberate attempts used for influencing people for the
   political, religious gains. In this research paper, efforts were made to
   classify Propagandist text from Non-Propagandist text using supervised
   machine learning algorithms. Data was collected from the news sources
   from July 2018-August 2018. After annotating the text, feature
   engineering is performed using techniques like term frequency/inverse
   document frequency (TF/IDF) and Bag of words (BOW). The relevant
   features are supplied to support vector machine (SVM) and Multinomial
   Naive Bayesian (MNB) classifiers. The fine tuning of SVM is being done
