   including Russian and American partisan groups, and explored how their
   operations deviated from canonical state propaganda marked by symbols of
   national identity and heroic masculinity. The results show that the
   visual frames employed by the Internet Research Agency are designed to
   embody the vox populi with relatable, familiar, or attractive faces of
