   and authentic newsletters, with the interest of causing certain effects
   on the reader, identified here as the potential voter. Thus, the results
   point to the emergence of a conflict between supposed left and right
   ideals. In this conflict, Jair Bolsonaro is constructed as the
   protagonist, through an image of a hero of the country. For which a
   speech of glorification is used, through the vision of pathos, trying to
   cause in the reader feelings of patriotism and hope. Fernando Haddad, in
   turn, is constructed as an antagonist, through the use of inciting aims,
   which try to convince the reader of certain information and, also, of
   the pathos aim which, unlike the previous use, is used to cause the
