   reconceptualize our understanding of Russian influence to understand
   this high level of contestation. While the current understanding of
   Russian influence is characterized as a problem of unwanted information
   flows, we argue that we also need to take seriously the ideological
   influence that the Russia regime has in the USA-that the appeal of the
   Russian regime's conservative and populist ideology can help to explain
